      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Distributed Message Queue",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Distributed Message Queue",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "i7361ozjiFa6qSDLW24-l",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 233.90492248535156,
      "y": 243.58090209960938,
      "width": 631.1595458984375,
      "height": 1075,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIg",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 951439410,
      "version": 965,
      "versionNonce": 1182147310,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782653237010,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Questions?\n\nq. Event streaming platform ( kafka) or MQ ( rabbit MQ)?\nEvent streaming like kafka. i.e messages can be consumed \nrepeatedly by different consumer groups\n\nq. text only or support media?\nText only. size in kbs\n\nq. how many producers and consumers?\nconfigurable\n\nq. delivery semantics?\nAll. At most once, at least once, and exactly once\n\nq. optimise for latency or throupput\nconfigurable\n\nq. support data retention\nYes, configurable\n\nq. order of consumption?\nyes, imp, same as production\n\n\nFunctional req:\n- Producers producing a message and sending to MQ\n- Consumers consuming the message\n- message can be consumed by multiple consumers in different CG\n- support text only messages\n- support retention\n- support all delivery semantics\n- configurable latency and throuhput\n- order of messages in important and should be same as \nproduction\n\n\nNFR:\nAvaialble\nreliable\nScalable\nlatency / throuput ( config)\nDurable",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Questions?\n\nq. Event streaming platform ( kafka) or MQ ( rabbit MQ)?\nEvent streaming like kafka. i.e messages can be consumed \nrepeatedly by different consumer groups\n\nq. text only or support media?\nText only. size in kbs\n\nq. how many producers and consumers?\nconfigurable\n\nq. delivery semantics?\nAll. At most once, at least once, and exactly once\n\nq. optimise for latency or throupput\nconfigurable\n\nq. support data retention\nYes, configurable\n\nq. order of consumption?\nyes, imp, same as production\n\n\nFunctional req:\n- Producers producing a message and sending to MQ\n- Consumers consuming the message\n- message can be consumed by multiple consumers in different CG\n- support text only messages\n- support retention\n- support all delivery semantics\n- configurable latency and throuhput\n- order of messages in important and should be same as \nproduction\n\n\nNFR:\nAvaialble\nreliable\nScalable\nlatency / throuput ( config)\nDurable",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
