    {
      "id": "zXJXWSKcjUys9b3x73G4Q",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 5513.579541800827,
      "y": 832.0195842108068,
      "width": 677.739501953125,
      "height": 700,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bMa",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1801705522,
      "version": 464,
      "versionNonce": 441279346,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782665648673,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "7. State storage\n\nKeeps mapping between partitions and consumers\nand consumed offset for consumer group for each partition\nWe need a KV store like Redis, zookeper,\nkafka uses kafka brokers now. earlier was using zookerper\n\n\n\n\n\n8. Metadata storage\ninfo about topic like \n- number of partitions\n- retention period\n- distribution of replication ( distriution plan)\n\nKV store like zookeeper\n\n\n9. Zookeeper\n\nzookeeper has hierarchical metadata store used for service discovery\nleader election.\n\nIts strengths are strong consistency, watches, ephemeral nodes, \nand coordination primitives that make it \nideal for distributed system coordination.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "7. State storage\n\nKeeps mapping between partitions and consumers\nand consumed offset for consumer group for each partition\nWe need a KV store like Redis, zookeper,\nkafka uses kafka brokers now. earlier was using zookerper\n\n\n\n\n\n8. Metadata storage\ninfo about topic like \n- number of partitions\n- retention period\n- distribution of replication ( distriution plan)\n\nKV store like zookeeper\n\n\n9. Zookeeper\n\nzookeeper has hierarchical metadata store used for service discovery\nleader election.\n\nIts strengths are strong consistency, watches, ephemeral nodes, \nand coordination primitives that make it \nideal for distributed system coordination.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
